{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"394a6b1c-6115-4943-8c06-f991440ab956","content":"**Yes, there is a framework compatibility issue.** MSTest v3 dropped support for **.NET 5.0** (and all non-LTS frameworks below .NET 6.0). You must retarget your project to at least **`net6.0`** (or newer, e.g., `net8.0`) before upgrading to MSTest v3.\n\n### What you need to do:\n\n1. **Update `TargetFramework`** in your `.csproj` from `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or later).\n2. **Upgrade MSTest packages** to v3.\n3. Review any other breaking changes (assertion overloads, `DataRow` constructors, timeout behavior, etc.).\n\nWould you like me to proceed with the migration? I can use the MSTest v2→v3 migration skill to handle this end-to-end.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7fbd8960-9a90-46f2-9e65-9d8bd7192af9","outputTokens":207},"id":"9c7a5777-834d-4c8b-add4-64e692dced56","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:21:45.450Z","parentId":"46e59aab-c11e-4656-a09d-98245a30178c"}
